In his weekly address, President Trump speaks about his recent interactions with American troops and veterans, emphasizing the unity and shared purpose that exists within the Armed Forces. He encourages Americans to draw inspiration from the love and loyalty exhibited by service personnel and to work towards healing divisions within the country. The President emphasizes the importance of remembering shared values, speaking out against hatred, treating fellow citizens with love and affection, and honoring the sacrifices of heroes. He asks every American to make a promise to support and renew the sacred bonds of loyalty for those who have fought for the country. The President concludes by stating that unity, honoring history, and striving for peace among one another will allow the nation to remain a force for peace globally.